# System Architecture Rules

## Core Principle

The Shaivra system is composed of independent services.

Agents must respect service boundaries.

---

# Core Components


Ingestion System
Global Graph
GraphRAG Retrieval Engine
Shaivra Application


Each component has a distinct responsibility.

---

# Global Graph

Global Graph is the canonical intelligence dataset.

Responsibilities:

- entity storage
- relationship storage
- narrative clustering
- signal indexing

Technology:


Memgraph
Qdrant


The Global Graph service owns the data model.

---

# Retrieval Engine

GraphRAG retrieval engine is read-only.

Responsibilities:

- hybrid graph + vector retrieval
- context assembly
- hypothesis exploration

It must never modify graph data.

---

# Ingestion System

Ingestion is responsible for:

- collecting sources
- normalizing signals
- filtering documents

It outputs normalized signals.

---

# Message Queue

All pipeline stages communicate through a message queue.

Preferred technology:


Redpanda


Benefits:

- backpressure
- replay
- parallel processing

---

# Service Isolation

Code changes must respect module boundaries.

Allowed modifications:


/global-graph


Disallowed modifications:


/frontend
/ingestion
/infrastructure


If architectural changes are required:


STOP
REQUEST APPROVAL


---

# Deployment Model

Each component runs as an independent container.

Example:


global-graph-service
retrieval-service
ingestion-service


All services communicate through APIs or queues.

---

# Performance Goals


retrieval latency < 200ms
vector search < 100ms
graph traversal < 100ms